rom-Friedrichshafen-297x223.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-120x90.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-768x576.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-696x522.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-1068x801.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-560x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-80x60.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153038/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-265x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb20 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-264194\">Friedrichshafen is a beautiful place to hold a trade show.</figcaption></figure><h3>EUROBIKE Moves to Frankfurt</h3><p>The move, at least in part, is a response to the recent uptick in cycling’s global popularity. For an enterprise that makes its hay off international patrons and partnerships, Frankfurt makes a lot of sense – it houses the European Central Bank, making it a longtime magnate for venture-capitalized innovation. And as the geographic heart of Europe, it’s hard to beat Frankfurt’s tourist appeal. The relocation thus ameliorates two major barriers to its growth — physical accessibility and capital.</p><p>For show-goers, that should mean easier access and cheaper flights, and the possibility of improved lodging for guests (no more staying in another country, and commuting to the show by boat?).</p><p>In spite of previous Eurobike shows operating out of Messe Friedrichshafen’s giant hangers, EUROBIKE claims that Messe Frankfurt offers even more space for exhibitors with more product segments and increased content.</p><figure id=\"attachment_264195\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-264195\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2.jpg\" alt=\"Eurobike presentation at messe Friedrichshafen \" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-265x198.jpg 265w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/06153044/Eurobike-2022-moved-to-Frankfurt-images-from-Friedrichshafen-2-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-264195\">We can only hope there will still be dance routines to highlight new product.</figcaption></figure><h3>EUROBIKE’s New Concept</h3><p>It’s apparent from the press release that EUROBIKE’s latest partnership with “the world’s largest trade fair, conference and event organizer”, Messe Frankfurt, is the impetus. Messe Frankfurt has the majority pull and knows how to catch the enthusiast’s eye. Now, it seems that the multidisciplinary world of cycling has caught Messe’s.</p><p>The next major tune-up on order: EUROBIKE is moving the annual showcase up in 2022. The new mid-July dates are a shift from the late August/early September shows of yore. It’s a big logistic change that’s intended to account for the bike industry’s manufacturing and consumer cycles.</p><p>Honestly, the whole ‘reconceptualization’ vision feels a bit amorphous, and largely driven by a high-gear partnership and warmly global locale. But, that’s not a truth the organization shies from. In fact, EUROBIKE seems to announce its growth and patron reach without reserve. &nbsp;As far as experience is concerned, it states that 2022 will be “an experience for retail customers and a marketplace for industry and retailers. In short, the meeting place for all those who make up the sector.”</p><p>But, any EUROBIKE veteran who fears the move might be an exodus from tradition, the event maker offers comfort: “As always, the EUROBIKE concept in Frankfurt will be characterized by handling, experiencing, trying out and test-driving the products…In Frankfurt, the two worlds of cycling – sport/performance/competition and mobility/lifestyle – will unite.”</p><p>Learn more at <a href=\"https://www.eurobike-frankfurt.com/en/\">EUROBIKE-Frankfurt.com.</a></p></div></div>","author":"Jilli Cluff","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4b12c95a5077957ea4321ec3979584abd073b6783bce529ee4dc2564d14b15c7","category":"Cycling"}